        "text": "The Berne Convention for the Protection of Literary and Artistic Works ([[Berne Convention]]) (The Berne Convention of 1886) is currently the International Treaty which provides the scope for protection of Video Games as a Copyright. This protection can be drawn from the wide definition of \"Literary and Artistic Work\" Article 2 of the Convention, which reads as:"
